q_text: The bird was tired, where did it land?
q_op3: on the head of a man
taskA_pos:
Roof is the upper covering of a building.
Birds land over buildings when they're tired.
taskA_neg:
Cage is a box used for confinement.
Birds won't want to be confined.
Sky is the upper region of earth filled with air.
Sky isn't a place to land on.
Head is the upper part of body.
Birds won't land on the head of a man.
Countryside is the land in a rural area.
Birds may land anywhere, not only in rural areas.
taskB: Roof is the upper covering of a building where birds land on when they're tired. Sky isn't a place to land on and birds may land anywhere, not only in countryside. Birds won't land on things in the other options.
